@node "System" "System requirements"
@{b}System requirements@{ub}

  To use Dr.Hpgl you need at least an Amiga or WinUAE and
  at least Workbench 2.04.

  Dr.Hpgl optionally requires an installed PageStream package to work
  together with it.

@endnode

@node "ques" "Usage"
@{b}Usage@{ub}

  The main program: Dr.Hpgl
  =========================

  To start Dr.Hpgl, doubleclick the icon.

  A simple window appears. This window has only one function, it shows a
  preview of the drawing. You can easily control the program by menu
  commands and the shortcuts for them.

  Here lies the explanations of the menu commands:
  ================================================

  Project / Open [RA+O]
  ---------------------

  Shows a file requester to select a drawing file in the form of DR2D.
  This filetype is a general 2d drawing format on the Amiga. You can
  create such files with the following programs (not a full list):

   - PageStream (full featured DTP package for 6 platforms, commercial)
     www.grasshopperllc.com
   - Typesmith (vector font editor for AmigaOS, abandonware)
   - Metaview (viewer and converter for a lot of drawing formats, freeware)
     http://user.cs.tu-berlin.de/~jonash/noframe_english.html
   - ProPage (Amiga, abandonware)
   - ProDraw (Amiga, abandonware)

   The file for opening must not has a DR2D "extension". Dr.Hpgl looks
   inside the file to decide wheter is or not a suitable drawing.

   Project / Plot [RA+P]
   ---------------------

   The main part of Dr.Hpgl. A small window appear to show the size of the
   drawing in mm. The user can set the output device name as the following
   examples describes:

    - par: (the standard parallel port)
    - par00: (e.g. IOblix external parallel port)
    - ram: (saves Output.hpgl file to the ram disk)

   Project / Preferences
   ---------------------

   A window appears that is let the user to set some of the working
   parameters of the program.

   PageStream/Leech drawing [RA+L]
   -------------------------------

   If there is a running PageStream with an active document, this function
   brings the selected texts and drawings to Dr.Hpgl. This is a very handy
   function because you won't need to export the graphics from your document.


@endnode

